caption: Got the house special noodle. It was heavy on oil (even though I selected less oil) and not very flavorful. The beef was not too tender and overall nothing spectacular about the dish but nice when the craving hits. I enjoyed the complimentary mung bean tea for dine in. Service was good but ordering is all done online.
Good service,  and good food...different style of Chinese  Food Szechuan Spicy delicious

Beef noodle was spicy and noodle was good. Extra noodle event now. Beef was rib but too much mussels, oily and smelly for me. Next time I will try pork rib.. Pork dumpling was really good. Sweet and little spicy. Bean soup(cold) was ok. Sweet taste cold tea.
Very good noodles and soup but the beef includes muscle pieces that makes it very chewy. Dumplings were great and good sauce.

Currently giving free extra noodles with entree purchases. The texture of the noodles were perfectly chewy and matched the dishes very well. Should've asked for more spice in my Zajiang noodles. The tomato beef noodles don't come spicy and we're very flavorful.

If you are looking for delicious spicy food this is the place. There is spicy food for hot and cold weather... basically spicy food for all year round.  For those who are not into spicy food there are deliciously dished for you as well. The tomato beef stew noodles would be a good recommendation. It's like a beef tomato broth with the chinese noodles, tomato, and beef chunks.  During covid-19, they added plastic screens between each table. There is a contactless temperature stand at the door; and hand sanitizer as well. Ordering is now done with a QRC scan. You scan the code to get your menu and you can order from there - no app to download.  If you have multiple people in your party, everyone can can and delete dishes on the ordering site... based on the QR code everyones page updates in real time. Once you select an item you can order, add more, and checkout all on the site. They bring your food, come to refill water, and bring take out boxes as needed. If you perfer not to us the website to pay, you have the option to select pay at resturant.  Enjoyed coming here before Covid-19, but now during these times feel happy that we can enjoy the delicious food in a carefully restaurant.

Mian is a favorite of mine. We've been here before several times before 2020 (we took my parents here, my in-laws here, our friends here) because their noodles are amazing and the flavor is fantastic. Plus, there aren't many restaurants on Hawaii that don't feel like "Japanese fusion".  Since the pandemic, we've had takeout from Mian a few times. The noodles travel surprisingly well and the dumplings also taste almost as good as if you were dining in. (In comparison, we've had noodles and dumplings from a closer area in Aiea where we live and they are nowhere as good even though we bring it back much more quickly than from Mian in town.)  I would definitely recommend this place for any of its items (but ask for "mild mild mild mild" if you cannot take heat at all)!
I came here because the line for Chengdu Taste is too long.  The noodle soup here is really nice, especially for a rainy day. 😍

We had the jajian mian and the short rib noodles. My wife studied in Chendu, Sichuan, and she said that the jajian mian tasted just like her college experience. The short rib noodles were also very flavorful. We missed these Sichuan spices and the noodles really hit the spot.
Cheap but great noodles; usually order a noodle + small plates.
(Translated by Google) The portion size is not big  (Original) 份量不大味道一般

(Translated by Google) I ate Intestine noodle and it was good because there were a lot of giblets & daechang It's very greasy and spicy, but I enjoyed it!  (Original) Intestine 누들 먹었는데 곱창&대창이 많아서 좋았어요ㅎㅎ 상당히 기름지고 매콤한데 맛있게 먹었어요!

I went with my friend and it was both our first times there. We loved it! You need to do a temperature check in the front, there are plastic sheets between tables for safety, and you order and ask for a tab through a QR reader/website. Food was super good too. Highly reccomend!!

Delicious Sichuan noodles dishes! The broth is very flavorful and noodles were cooked to al dante. Their dishes can be a little too spicy for someone who’s not used to eating spicy foods so make sure to request “little spicy” or “not spicy”.  If you are ordering takeout, you could use their online ordering system to order ahead of time to minimize wait time. You could pay online or at the restaurant when you pick up.  It is located at the 808 Center across the street from Walmart. Valet parking only so you may want to park on the street and walk over. There’s another Sichuan restaurant on the second floor that serves mainly appetizers and entree dishes don’t get them mixed up (but I’m sure that one is good too!)
Excellent noodles! I like it when I can order without the dish being spicy. Will go back again when I want to eat a noodle dish.
Great place to dine for noodles! Spare ribs and dumplings a must

The food is delicious, and so reasonably priced! They open at 5 PM and they have a cool camera thing to check temperatures before seating patrons. They also have QR codes so you can see the menu and order through your phone. I loved the heat from my cold Sichuan noodles and my husband really enjoyed the hot and sour wonton.
Excellent handmade noodles

I have had the beef pickles noodles many times at a different location. The broth has never tasted so plain from today's order from this location! It's basically watery mixed with a teaspoon of salt! Without any of its usual mala flavor unique to this noodle dish. I was also only given half togo cup of the soup, barely enough for half portion of the noodles. The food also arrived cold so it did not help!
very small portion of the noodles, very expensive. No test beside spicy and salty.
Delicious and clean place!

Friendly and good service. They offer mung beans water I thought it was very healthy.  Valet in the building. It is in the mechanical tower parking with the parking attendant.  If you are in a hurry, it’s best to park somewhere flat and walk over.

Thought the dumplings were really tasty and some of the spicy dishes. Lots of variety and option to order a lot and share family style. Byob always nice. Nice to see different chinese options popping up here and there.

Fantastic dishes, friendly service & well deserved pricing make Mian one of the places I can't wait to return to. The noodles are made in house, boasting a pleasurable chewiness missing from most similar establishments. Nothing is too salty or too sweet, juuuusstt right. You may find the spicy dishes too flavorful at first but since you won't be able to put down your chopsticks you'll soon discover each bite is ever more satisfying than the last.. do yourself a favor and invite your friends or family to Mian for a memorable dining experience ;D

(Translated by Google) Authentic Chinese Szechuan food. I thought it was American Chinese food. After I came in, I found that the noodle taste was very Chengdu. Praise!  (Original) Authentic Chinese Szechuan food.  以为是美式中餐，进来以后发现面味道很正很成都。好评！
food and prices are great! can get really busy at dinner so go early or plan to wait in line.
So goooood!
Delicious with some. Heat and authentic noodles

Service was excellent! The star of the night for me were the dumplings. So good! The noodles were also very good and is mala spicy for those who like a flare. The mung bean soup/drink was also very refreshing with the noodles. There was a promotion going on where you get a side of potatoes for orders $30+ and I really enjoyed that as well.

I've spent more than 35 years in Asia and I've eaten a lot of noodles. These were some of the best I've had. Really fresh with great texture. Be careful of how spicy you order.  They can really make them hot.

Very quality noodles. Actually, the best in town. I like the beef soup noodle in particular. It is clean, and the ambiance is intimate . The staff is very friendly. I enjoy the iced bean drink very much.
I feel just regular noodles

(Translated by Google) We had Chengdu jar noodles and gizzards and celery spicy noodles. Both are dry mixed noodles. Mochimochi noodles and spicy ingredients are the best match! It was delicious (^^)  (Original) 成都ジャージャー麺と砂肝とセロリのスパイシー麺をいただきました。どちらもドライな混ぜ麺。もっちもちの麺とピリ辛具材がベストマッチ！美味しかったです(^^)

Get your mouth muscles puckered up for a lovely Sichuan peppercorn tingle!🔥 So tasty! I had the ground pork noodles w the fried egg and Choi sum. Dumplings are a must and the sauce is divine. They also serve you mung bean "tea" which has a mildly sweet taste and really helps temper the spice 😉 and they come in cute dictator mugs heheh. This is not your average Chinese spot, definitely recommend for noodle lovers and friends.

Fantastic place for Sichuan style noodles! I love the chewy texture of the noodles. 11/10 for the noodles alone. The sauce for the noodles are also great. I would definitely go for the dry noodles over the soup noodles as I feel the flavors are richer and more developed. The dumplings and the wontons are also delicious and should definitely be ordered. They also serve a mung bean drink which really helps to cut the spiciness of their dishes. Its a little sweet and when its hot out this is one of my favorite drinks.
Super authentic

The food here is very good. I tried the spicy beef noodle soup, and boy it was spicy. I would eat here again. Not the shop’s problem, but it was hard to find parking. The valet machine garage thingy they got on site can only use by valet, and they weren’t there when we came.
(Translated by Google) good to eat  (Original) 好吃

We came here for lunch on a Sunday. The service was pretty good-the waitress was sweet and attentive. The interior was cleanly, and it wasn't too busy around the time we went which was around noon. Food got to us relatively quickly. Parking is valet only, so you'll have to pay a small parking fee when you arrive, though not unreasonable depending on how long you stay (between $4.00 - $6.00).  The only reason I'm giving it a 3/5 is because the food was not to my liking, though not because of anything they did wrong but because of my own perception prior to coming there. As a ramen lover, I went here off a recommendation from a friend (who also thought this was a ramen shop based on the photos). I got the sichuan noodles with pork and a fried egg. I was disappointed with my dish because I wasn't aware the dish I ordered did not come with broth which heavily offset the taste for me. That, and I'm really not a fan of the fried egg in my noodles since my tastes are usually adjusted for the boiled egg you get in a ramen bowl. The Mung Bean soup they serve you when you first sit down was another thing I wasn't prepared for. I misheard the waitress and thought she said "Miso Soup" when she brought it over, so I was not prepared for the cold sweet liquid that hit my mouth a few seconds later.  All in all, the food isn't bad if you like Chinese Noodles and it was definitely a new experience for me to try. However,  if you normally eat ramen and walk in with a "ramen-mindset", then you are in for a rude awakening.

Noodles were delicious! The extra spare ribs I added on went perfectly with the spicy sour broth. Broth wasn’t quite as spicy as I usually like but it was enough to clear your sinuses. I’m still sweating as I write this. Most of the spare ribs were pretty tender. This is one restaurant in Honolulu I will continue to patronize in the future, which is rare for me. I also have to mention the reasonable prices. They even give you a stamp card you can redeem for $15 credit in store. However  you will only receive the card on your first visit and not actually get it stamped.

This place is great! You can order extra noodles for free when you buy a bowl of noodles. The extra noodles also comes with matching broth of whichever noodle soup you ordered, which is a bonus. Tastes amazing I definitely would recommend the house beef noodle soup. They have a nice atmosphere, parking is valet only so you can save some money finding some street parking. Very authentic, can be pretty spicy too.
Pictures can tell!!!!!
Loved the spicy noodles and soup. Waitress was lovely, ambience fantastic and food delicious.
It's for those who like spicy food, however the items we had were just average, they couldn't even serve hot tea. Not that great.

What a great place. Noodle was delicious and service was excellent. I normally don't eat spicy food but it was very managable especially with the sweet complimentary bean water to help. The cold noodle was delicious and I love the dumplings too. Highly recommend it.
(Translated by Google) In Honolulu, the taste is authentic, spicy and not spicy, good, worth a try  (Original) 在Honolulu 来说，口味算正宗，有辣和不辣，不错，值得一试
WOW!!!!

Went here for date night. The location is easy to walk to from Walmart and they do have valet parking. Went here for date night and the foods legit! I love it! First Chinese place I’d def bring my chinese friends too. It’s a chain and it does have two other locations on the mainland.  We decided to get spicy beef and egg with beef as the appetizers and got the picked beef noodle and intestine noodle. Everything has amazing flavor and the noodles are PERFECT! As my mom would say about the noodle, “yo jer!” It me, it’s better then al dente, it has some spring/bounce to its noodle chew, but it doesn’t means it’s chewy like rubber or tough meat. It’s amazing noodle texture. The broth is flavorful and the spicy heat is enough and not over powering. You can ask for water but you get mung bean soup as the drink which has a slight sweet taste. It’s delicious!!! I can’t wait to go back
(Translated by Google) Authentic and delicious Chinese noodles. Bowl and chicken are my favorite!  (Original) 正宗美味的中国面条 碗杂+鸡杂是我的最爱！
Fantastically spicy and tasty.  Was very pleased with my meal.  Service was friendly and food was served very quickly after ordering.  Simple layout, but comfortable.
Authentic Sichuan noodles!

Updated APR2018  Chengdu Tasty has been moved to third floor so the owner opened a noodle shop in place of it. The noodles was good and decent and very authentic. The spiciness was on point. Noodles is just a little bit undercook and a little hard to chew. Setbacks was the volume. Not much contained in the bowl and add-ons of any sides are expensive. They give you one free refill of plain noodle.  Service was pretty bad. The server had a really bad attitude. I couldn’t get the noodle refill without wasting my breath to explain to him I can finish what I order. After all, I’m paying for my food so why can’t I order more? No one was serving us while we were raising our hands and the owner ended up helping us. We also had to get the water jug ourselves from the front and pour our own water. They have these relaxing green bean water to help soothe the spiciness in the noodle.  There is no parking available in the building so it is best to park across the street in the Walmart parking lot.

Awesome place to get good authentic Chinese noodles.  Located in the 808 building next to Hawaii Hot Pot behind the parking lot for Walmart.  Very nice Place good prices and fast service.  No alcohol served here but you can be BYOB.
